500 g Ground Beef
2 unit Artisan Bun
2 tbsp BBQ Seasoning
340 g Sweet Potato
28 g Spring Mix
90 mL Dill Pickle, sliced
¼ cup Panko Breadcrumbs
4 tbsp BBQ Sauce
4 tbsp Mayonnaise
1 tbsp Whole Grain Mustard
1 tbsp Oil*
0.31 tsp Salt*
0.06 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, preheat oven to 450°F. Wash and dry all produce.  Cut sweet potatoes into 1/2-inch wedges. Add sweet potatoes, half the BBQ Seasoning and 1 tbsp oil (dbl for 4 ppl) to a parchment-lined baking sheet. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat. Roast in the middle of the oven, flipping halfway through, until tender and golden-brown, 20-22 min.

Add mayo and mustard to a small bowl. Season with pepper, then stir to combine. Drain pickles. Halve buns.

Add beef, panko, remaining BBQ Seasoning, half the BBQ Sauce and 1/4 tsp salt (dbl for 4 ppl) to a medium bowl. Season with pepper, then combine. (TIP: If you prefer a firmer patty, add an egg to the mixture! For 4 ppl, add two eggs.) Form mixture into four 4-inch wide burger patties (eight patties for 4 ppl).

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium heat. When hot, add patties to the dry pan. Pan-fry until cooked through, 4-5 min per side. (NOTE: For 4 ppl, don't overcrowd the pan. Pan-fry the patties in two batches!) Transfer patties to another baking sheet. Spread remaining BBQ sauce over tops of patties. Roast in the top of the oven until BBQ sauce is warmed through, 4-5 min.

While patties roast, add buns directly to the top rack of the oven, cut-side up. Toast until golden-brown, 3-4 min. (TIP: Keep an eye on them so they don't burn!)

Spread some of the zesty mayo onto bottom buns. Top with pickles, patties, spring mix and top buns. Divide burgers and sweet potato wedges between plates. Serve remaining zesty mayo on the side for dipping.